<h1 id=3D"ChannelsSD:PaymentInitiationCAPAPIV1toV2upgrade-UserStoryTraceabi=
lity"><span>User Story Traceability</span></h1>
<p><span>Business requirements: NA</span></p>
<p><span>Feature Page:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.a=
u/display/ARTC/Divisions+-+Customer+portal+screen+analysis" rel=3D"nofollow=
">N</a>A</span></p>
<h1 id=3D"ChannelsSD:PaymentInitiationCAPAPIV1toV2upgrade-SolutionOverview"=
><span>Solution Overview</span></h1>
<p><span>As part of Feb 2026 ERM, the Payment Initiation CAP API will be up=
lifted to V2 version in order to prepare for the upcoming POM9 migration (w=
hich is expected to happen in May 2026 &amp; until then, V2 version of the =
CAP API will continue to consume POM7). The V2 version of the Payment Initi=
ation CAP API will have a different request &amp; response payload structur=
e as compared to V1, which means, the corresponding CAP API request and res=
ponse mapping will change in the Payments EXP API. The mapping changes are =
detailed in the <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/AR=
TC/Channels+SD+%3A+Payment+Initiation+CAP+API+-V1+to+V2+upgrade#ChannelsSD:=
PaymentInitiationCAPAPIV1toV2upgrade-EXPAPItoPaymentInitiationV2CAPAPIMappi=
ng" rel=3D"nofollow">EXPAPItoPaymentInitiationV2CAPAPIMapping</a> section a=
nd these mapping changes will be applicable in the&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://=
confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC/exp-galaxy-payment-v2#expgalaxyp=
aymentv2-POST/paymentCreate" rel=3D"nofollow">exp-galaxy-payment-v2 - POST =
/paymentCreate</a> and <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/dis=
play/ARTC/exp-galaxy-payment-v2#expgalaxypaymentv2-POST/paymentCreateForNew=
BeneficiaryFEB26" rel=3D"nofollow">exp-galaxy-payment-v2 - POST /paymentCre=
ateForNewBeneficiary</a> EXP APIs</span> "<strong><span style=3D"color: rgb=
(23,43,77);">postPaymentsController.helper.ts</span></strong>" component to=
 handle the following,</p>
<ul>
<li>EXP API request to CAP API request mapping, the code changes will be re=
quired in the <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/=
repos/galaxy-payment-microfrontend/browse/api/server/api/helpers/postPaymen=
tsController.helper.ts#84" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">generat=
ePaymentsRequestDataForCAP</a> method/function.</li>
<li>CAP API response to EXP API response mapping, the code changes will be =
required in the&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projec=
ts/WDP/repos/galaxy-payment-microfrontend/browse/api/server/api/helpers/pos=
tPaymentsController.helper.ts#12" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">=
transformPaymentsResponseFromCAPToUI</a> method/function.</li>
</ul>
<p>Sequence flow is as below</p>
<p><map id=3D"gliffy-map-2144547355-5715" name=3D"gliffy-map-2144547355-571=
5"></map></p>
<table width=3D"100%" class=3D"gliffy-macro-table">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<table class=3D"gliffy-macro-inner-table">
<caption align=3D"bottom">
</caption>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><img style=3D"border: none; width: 1331px;" usemap=3D"#gliffy-map-21445=
47355-5715" src=3D"8dd76a2361b77fa308424b8b2e4654d1bf99d0d666fad3618297aa94=
ecd1a715" alt=3D"" class=3D"gliffy-macro-image" width=3D"468" height=3D"445=
"></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p></p>
