<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><u><strong>Note:</strong></u></span=
> In order to handle the insufficient account balance scenario, in the UI, =
check for "apiStatus =3D=3D=3D 202" instead of 201 as V2 will no longer ret=
urn 201 for RJCT scenarios, instead it will return 202 status code. So ther=
e will be a code change required in the <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.we=
stpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/galaxy-payment-microfrontend/browse/ui/src/=
components/PaymentConfirmation/PaymentConfirmation.tsx#211" class=3D"extern=
al-link" rel=3D"nofollow">PaymentConfirmation.tsx#211</a> &amp; <a href=3D"=
https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/galaxy-payment-micr=
ofrontend/browse/ui/src/components/ReturnConfirmation/ReturnConfirmation.ts=
x#189" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">ReturnConfirmation.tsx#189<=
/a> to handle the same. Sample code change for payment confirmation will be=
 as below(similar code changes would be required in the return confirmation=
 as well),</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">if (apiSt=
atus =3D=3D=3D 202) {    =20
      if (payment?.paymentInformation?.paymentInformationStatus =3D=3D=3D '=
RJCT') {
        const hasInsufficientBalance =3D
          payment?.paymentStatusReasonInformation.find(
            (status) =3D&gt; status.reason =3D=3D=3D 'AV04'
          );

        message =3D hasInsufficientBalance
          ? messageForInsufficientAccountBalance
          : messageForGenericPaymentStatusReason;
      }
    }</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"ChannelsSD:PaymentInitiationCAPAPIV1toV2upgrade-OtherErrorscenari=
os">Other Error scenarios</h1>
<p>Following error scenarios should be treated as generic error scenarios a=
nd generic error message should be displayed on the UI accordingly.</p>
<ul>
<li>payId mismatch &amp; payId deregistered scenarios: The V2 API will no l=
onger carry out the payId lookup, instead, FIS will do it when processing t=
he payment(only if the payId resolution was done 30 mins prior to processin=
g the payment). Payments team has confirmed that for any payId mismatch and=
 payId deregistered scenarios, the V2 CAP API will return 202 status code w=
ith RJCT, so Channels can continue to display generic error message for the=
se scenarios based on the same. <u><strong>Note:</strong></u> The ISO error=
 codes are yet to be confirmed by the payments team for these scenarios.</l=
i>
<li>For a debit account updated to one of the following statuses(after paym=
ent is initiated), FIS will reject the payment when it is trying to process=
 the payment. The V2 CAP API will return 202 status code with RJCT for any =
such FIS payment related errors and Channels can continue to display generi=
c error message for any such scenarios based on the 202 status code with RJ=
CT=20
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p>Payee Account Status</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span data-teams=3D"true">SUSPENDED</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">CLOSED</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span data-teams=3D"true">PART_SUSPENDED</span><=
/td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span data-teams=3D"true">PART_FROZEN</span></td=
>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span data-teams=3D"true">FROZEN</span></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div></li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"ChannelsSD:PaymentInitiationCAPAPIV1toV2upgrade-Non-FunctionalReq=
uirements">Non-Functional Requirements</h1>
